# `design/` is the UX example source

When refactoring the extension UI (new tab, widgets, settings), treat the root `design/` folder as the canonical **UX/layout examples** (in addition to `DESIGN.md`).

## Apply these patterns

- **Shell**: fixed top bar, HUD-like grid, scanline overlay.
- **Inputs**: terminal prompt prefix like `USER_LOG@TAB:>`.
- **Layout**: stable zones (left/center/right) or 12-col grid; avoid “auto masonry card soup”.
- **Style invariants**: 0px radius, hard offset shadows, Acid Green + Glitch Magenta accents.

## Implementation constraints (Tabocalypse)

- **Tailwind only**: use utilities + `@layer` in `apps/extension/entrypoints/newtab/tailwind.css` (no parallel CSS systems).
- **Icons**: `lucide-react` only; icon-only actions must have plain-language `aria-label`.
